{"id": "QmS4pXmpTWaM6YcSmeHifAAnNYPMCjxWqp9FKAipcAdEPp", "title": "Petting Gotchis: 1-hour grace period", "body": "FlameViper#7396 +3782\nhttps://dao.aavegotchi.com/t/petting-gotchis-1-hour-grace-period/1557/8\n\nHaving the timer activate exactly at 12 hours without any extra hour being granted/rolled back means you will have 7-15 extra minutes adding up each time you pet your gotchis to the point it ruins your schedule and you have to pet your gotchi at 3AM to 5AM. \nAdd a pet-all option which someone has already created.\nAdd a 1-59minute grace period where the timer resets right before the gotchi was petted. The timer doesn't go backwards neither forwards, it gives you a 1 hour window to pet your gotchi, the timer will be stable.\nThis is a plain fix that keeps the timer from creeping by a few minutes each time till it ruins your schedule.\nPeople will no longer have to use bots and stop having to ruin their sleep schedules.\nThis should be implemented right after the first round of BRS farming ends, at most before the end of this month.\nI do not see any risks whatsoever associated with this specific proposal.\n\nPlan B is to make things easy by allowing players to pet their gotchis 2 times in a day and a night whenever they choose in said day/afternoon and night/morning, just that they have to stay within the allocated time periods; 12:00-23:59 and 0:00-11:59 UTC\nYou can pet your gotchi before 23:59 and after 0:00 if you want both pets to count, just make sure you don't forget. This will keep the 12 hour cycle and make petting much more relaxing compared to metaphorically taking antibiotics at specific hours down to the minute.", "choices": ["Plan A", "Plan B", "Abstain"], "start": 1618351200, "end": 1619182800, "snapshot": "11507560", "state": "closed", "author": "0xDe34393312C0C1e97e404d18A04580E9610e063C", "space": {"id": "aavegotchi.eth", "name": "Aavegotchi"}, "votes": 51, "votes_data": [{"id": "QmTo2RQgBwGbvXi4GwjSsHER6KkfUGcZqgssS7SmnMZVY6", "voter": "0